    "body" : "<p>If you're already logged into the command line client try this:</p>\n\n<pre><code>mysql&gt; select user();\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>It will output something similar to this:</p>\n\n<pre><code>+----------------+\n| user()         |\n+----------------+\n| root@localhost |\n+----------------+\n1 row in set (0.41 sec)\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>In my example above, I was logged in as <code>root</code> from <code>localhost</code>.</p>\n\n<p>To find port number and other interesting settings use this command:</p>\n\n<pre><code>mysql&gt; show variables;\n</code></pre>\n"
